# Template for .sweep-patterns.local (which is gitignored — NEVER commit it).
# One extended-regex per line; matched case-insensitively against every
# tracked file by scripts/sweep.sh. Put the REAL banned strings only in
# .sweep-patterns.local, so they never appear in the repo itself.
#
# Typical categories:
# \bacme(corp|vpn)?\b        <- product / company names
# \bexample-internal\.com\b  <- internal hostnames
# \bjdoe|janedoe\b           <- real person names
# perm(:|-)[A-Za-z0-9]{10,}  <- API token shapes
#
# Prefix a line with NOADR: to scope it to code/tests only — matched
# case-SENSITIVELY against every tracked file EXCEPT docs/adr/* and CHANGELOG*
# (whose historical mentions are grandfathered). Use for real project-code /
# ticket-ID prefixes, e.g.:
# NOADR:\b(ABC|XYZ)-[0-9]     <- real issue prefixes -> should be PROJ-### in code/tests
